This paper deals with the control of dynamic agents in a network, which is a common topic in robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). The focus on maintaining network connectivity and avoiding collisions suggests that the paper may also fall under the multi-agent systems (cs.MA) category. The use of a navigation function framework and local feedback suggests that the paper may also be related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and swarm intelligence (cs.SI).
